<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JUL 94 / Other main points of Tecs survey
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Other main points in the survey, completed by 400 out of 1,200 Tec
directors:
Fifty-five per cent believe companies above a certain size should have to
register with the local Tec.
There was growing satisfaction with the progress of Investors in People, the
government - backed scheme for improving in-company training.
Sixty-seven per cent of directors from the private sector felt they would
not remain on a Tec board if they were no longer in the majority.
Fifty-one per cent - including 40 per cent of those from the private sector
 -believe in a return to a levy on training, which is Labour party policy.
Eighty-two per cent believe Tecs should be open to public scrutiny.
