<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JUL 94 / MacGregor denies involvement in 'details' of Railtrack
negotiation
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr John MacGregor, the transport secretary, said at a meeting of the Commons
employment committee yesterday that he had told members of the British Rail
board on June 9 that Railtrack's 5.7 per cent interim pay offer to the RMT
transport union conflicted with government guidelines.
However, Mr MacGregor denied he was involved in the 'details' of
negotiation. In a written memorandum to the committee, the Department of
Transport said that it had been made clear to Railtrack that any increases
in pay for signal workers had to be 'offset by improvements in efficiency
and productivity and the package must represent value for money'.
During his session with the committee Mr MacGregor said he hoped the two
sides would return to negotiations and there could be an early settlement of
the dispute.
