<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JUL 94 / Outcry as regulator moves to company
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Members of the group of investors complaining about Knight Williams, the
independent financial adviser, have written to the Treasury and to City
regulatory bodies expressing concern that a senior regulator has joined the
company, Alison Smith writes.
Knight Williams has recently appointed Mr Colin Pinnell to oversee its legal
and compliance department. Mr Pinnell was formerly head of legal services at
Fimbra, the self-regulating organisation for independent financial advisers.
The Securities and Investments Board, the City's chief watchdog, has already
discussed with Fimbra a number of complaints against Knight Williams.
Disgruntled investors are seeking assurances that the government and
regulators are satisfied there is no 'leak' of information from Fimbra to
Knight Williams about cases raised by complainants.
Past complaints have centred on the company's high charges and on investment
performance.
Mr John Williams, Knight Williams managing director, said yesterday that
while he had previously dealt with compliance matters he was increasingly
spending his time on other issues, and so Mr Pinnell had been appointed.
Both parties had agreed that there must be 'utter confidentiality' about
matters with which Mr Pinnell had been involved during his time at Fimbra,
he said.
</TEXT>
