FT  13 JUL 94 / N-site row intensifies
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By QUENTIN PEEL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Miners working on Germany's first proposed disposal site for long-term
nuclear waste yesterday appealed for police protection, after demonstrators
blocked access roads with makeshift huts, and dug tunnels to prevent the
delivery of the first containers of highly-radioactive waste. Up to 1,000
anti-nuclear protesters have blocked the roads around Gorleben, in lower
Saxony, where an interim storage facility has been built near the planned
long-term disposal site. Police have been instructed by the state
authorities, who oppose the disposal scheme, not to intervene, but the
federal government says interim storage can go ahead, pending proper
investigation of the mining site.
