<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUL 94 / International Company News: SHL shows solid growth
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SHL Systemhouse, a fast- growing Canadian computer service group, says that
margins are improving and profits are recovering quickly, writes Robert
Gibbens in Montreal.
Third-quarter revenues were up 24 per cent at CDollars 305m (USDollars
219.4m).
Net profit more than doubled to CDollars 5.9m, or 9 cents a share, from
CDollars 2.3m, or 5 cents, a year earlier.
The result brings net profit for nine months to CDollars 16m, or 27 cents a
share, up from CDollars 3.9m, or 9 cents, a year earlier, on revenues of
CDollars 864m, up 26 per cent.
Mr John Oltman, SHL chairman, said that the company was focusing on
improving operating margins further in the short term, while continuing to
develop markets in North and South America, Europe and Asia.
