<TEXT>
Two competing electronics industry partnerships, both aimed at the emerging
market for equipment used to provide interactive multimedia services, were
announced yesterday.
Sun Microsystems, the US computer company, has paired with Thomson Consumer
Electronics of France, while Digital Equipment, one of the largest US
computer manufacturers, will collaborate with General Instrument, a leading
US manufacturer of television set-top decoder boxes for the cable-TV
industry.
Sun and TCE said they would form a jointly-funded business unit that would
develop and market 'end-to-end solutions' for interactive television, home
shopping, distance learning and other on-line business and personal
services.
