FT  12 JUL 94 / International Company News: Good second-half growth boosts
Taiwanese bank
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURA TYSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hua Nan Commercial Bank, one of Taiwan's three main government-owned banks
dominating the local market, posted preliminary pre-tax earnings of
NTDollars 6.4bn (USDollars 239m) for the fiscal year ended June 30.
This was an increase of 21 per cent from a year earlier. However, analysts
cautioned that most of the growth had been in the second half of 1993, while
the first half of this year had been stagnant due to slower loan growth and
increasing pressure on interest rate spreads.
The bank also reported revenues of NTDollars 55.8bn, up 4.9 per cent from
1993.
Taiwan's 16 commercial banks set up since 1992 are aggressively expanding,
which will make it increasingly difficult for the three state-run commercial
banks to build their loan portfolios, analysts said.
