FT  12 JUL 94 / UK Company News: TBI makes Pounds 13.8m property sale
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TBI, the property investment and development company, has sold its office
building at Borehamwood, Herts, for Pounds 13.8m in cash to Postel,
generating a Pounds 1.05m surplus to the net book value.
The rental income from the building, which totals 79,502 sq ft with 286
parking places, is Pounds 1.17m per annum. Proceeds will be used to reduce
bank debt.
