</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Law Society of England and Wales and the French and Dutch-language
Brussels Bars have reached agreement, after two years of negotiations, on
the right of lawyers to practise under their home title in each other's
jurisdictions.
English solicitors will be able to practise under their established firm
names in Brussels from September 15 without registering on one of the
Brussels Bars' lists of foreign lawyers.
