<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUL 94 / Labour warns on gas deregulation
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Labour yesterday warned the government not to deregulate the domestic gas
market without consulting parliament.
Mr Martin O'Neill, Labour's energy spokesman, said: 'Political decisions on
the provision of fuel should be made by elected politicians rather than by
unaccountable regulators.'
He was reacting to a statement by Ms Clare Spottiswoode, the gas industry
regulator, that she would consider various ways to introduce wider
competition if the government failed to put forward a new gas bill in time
to meet the 1996 deadline to begin phasing in deregulation.
