<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUL 94 / Foreign banks face costs blow in London
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The costs of setting up and running an international bank branch in London
have continued to rise during the past two years - after a dip in 1992 - to
record levels in many cases.
The findings come in an analysis by Noel Alexander Associates, a consultancy
which specialises in financial statistics. It looked at four separate cases
 -setting up just a London representative office, or establishing a branch
in any one of three sizes.
The study showed, for example, that both the opening and annual costs of
setting up a small branch, at Pounds 2.14m and Pounds 984,000 respectively,
were above the previous records of Pounds 1.86m (in April 1993) and Pounds
963,900 (in February 1990).
The annual cost of running a medium-size branch was estimated at Pounds
2.24m, compared with Pounds 2.12m in April last year. The opening cost for
such a branch was Pounds 3.28m - above the level of last year but slightly
down on the record of Pounds 3.30m in February 1990.
The study also highlighted the notably higher costs of setting up a
representative office using an expatriate rather than a UK resident.
Start-up cost of such an office with an expatriate was estimated at Pounds
822,550, while with a local representative it falls to Pounds 273,590.
Annual running costs are also cheaper for the local option - Pounds 235,370
against Pounds 308,520.
A marked change compared with some previous years is that property costs
make up only a small proportion - about one-tenth - of the total
calculations. This is partly because, the consultancy says, the London
property market is such that it is possible to negotiate two or three years'
occupation rent-free.
Staff costs are the largest single element in the estimated budgets, ranging
up to three-quarters of the totals.
The number of foreign banks in London has been rising in recent years, and
is now more than 500.
Bank Case Studies. Noel Alexander Associates, 6 Broad Street Place,
Blomfield Street, London EC2M 7JU. Pounds 120.
</TEXT>
