<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUL 94 / Hyundai jail term suspended
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SEOUL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A Seoul high court yesterday suspended a three-year jail term for
embezzlement and election fraud imposed on Mr Chung Ju-yung, founder of
South Korea's Hyundai group, Reuter reports from Seoul. Mr Chung, 79, was
convicted last November of diverting more than Won50bn (Pounds 40.3m) from
the group he founded and funnelling the funds to his political party to
underwrite his 1992 presidential bid. The jail sentence imposed at the time
was for three years with no suspension.
